Virtualization Security
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Install and configure KVM virtualization with security hardening
Implement security controls for virtual machines
Create automated snapshot management systems
Develop backup and recovery procedures for VMs
Apply security best practices to virtualization infrastructure
Prerequisites
Before starting this lab, students should have:

Basic Linux command line proficiency
Understanding of virtualization concepts
Familiarity with shell scripting
Access to a Linux system with sudo privileges
