Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: KVM modules not loading

Solution: Verify CPU virtualization support in BIOS/UEFI settings
Check with: egrep -c '(vmx|svm)' /proc/cpuinfo
Issue: Permission denied errors with virsh

Solution: Ensure user is in libvirt group: sudo usermod -a -G libvirt $USER
Logout and login again or use: newgrp libvirt
Issue: Snapshot creation fails

Solution: Ensure VM disk format supports snapshots (qcow2)
Check disk space availability
Verify VM is not in transient state
Issue: Backup script fails for running VMs

Solution: Implement proper live backup with external snapshots
Ensure sufficient disk space for temporary snapshots
Handle blockcommit operations correctly
